                        <!-- Title -->
                        <h3 class="h3-md mt-5">WHY CANADA</h3>

                        <!-- Text -->
                        <p>
                            Canada is a North American country consisting of ten provinces and three territories.

It ranks among the highest in international measurements of government transparency, civil liberties, quality of life, economic freedom, and education.

Canada has been recognized as an education superpower. It offers a sound education system, friendly student environment and an immigration system that is open to everyone. One of the greatest aspects of studying abroad in Canada is that there is an option for students of all ages, whether you are in high school or in a graduate degree. If you are looking to study in student friendly place with great academic options and highly ranked universities or colleges, then you should consider studying in Canada.

Canadians place a great importance on learning, and have developed a first class education system with high standard. The country spends more on education (as a percentage of GDP) compared to the OECD average and is the second highest among G – 8 Countries.

Canada is lauded as one of the best places in the world to live.
                        </p>


