                        <!-- Title -->
                        <h3 class="h3-md mt-5">STUDY IN CANADA</h3>

                        <!-- Text -->
                        <p>
                            TOP REASONS TO STUDY IN CANADA:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>World-class – Quality education.
                            </li>
                            <li>Affordable education.
                            </li>
                            <li>United Nations ranked Canada as one of the best places in the world to live (in terms of Educational attainment, Life expectancy, National income and General quality of Life).

                            </li>
                            <li>Opportunity to work and co-op Programs are available.

                            </li>
                            <li>Up to 3-year Post-graduation Work Permit available

                            </li>
                            <li>The possibility of Immigration (may apply for Permanent residency without leaving Canada, please visit – (www.cic.gc.ca ) website for more information and 90 % outbound mobility has been settled there only.
                            </li>
                            <li>Future opportunities- Canada is among top 10 economies of the world as per latest report of WEF (World Economic Forum), provides you with the plethora of opportunities to establish your career in leading organizations, the potential labour shortage has been anticipated there.
                            </li>
                            <li>Over 8000 programs and 70+ public institutions offering Credentials.
                            </li>
                            <li>The safest place to survive.

                            </li>
                        </ul>


                    </div>
                    <div id="three" class="about-9-txt mb-40 pr-15 my-pt">

                        <!-- Title -->
                        <h3 class="h3-md mt-5">EDUCATION SYSTEM
                        </h3>

                        <!-- Text -->

                        <ul>
                            <li>In Canada, Institutes and other non-degree granting institutions primarily offer Diplomas and Certificate programs in numerous semi-professional and technical fields, while Universities focus on degree programs and University Colleges typically offer Degrees, Diplomas and Certificates.
                            </li>
                            <li>Diplomas and Certificates
                            </li>
                            <li>University transfer programs are offered at some colleges.

                            </li>
                            <li>Bachelor’s Degree
                            </li>
                            <li>Master’s Degree
                            </li>
                        </ul>


                    </div>
                    <div id="four" class="about-9-txt mb-40 pr-15 my-pt">

                        <!-- Title -->
                        <h3 class="h3-md mt-5">REQUIREMENTS</h3>

                        <ul>
                            <li>For Certificate Courses or Diploma : HSC with 60% and IELTS 6 bands each module
                            </li>
                            <li>For Bachelor Degree: HSC with 70% and IELTS 6.5 bands with no band less than 6.0 band
                            </li>

                            <li>For Postgraduate Certificate or Diploma Program: Bachelor Degree with 60% and IELTS 6.5 bands with 6.0 band in each module
                            </li>
                            <li>For Masters Degree: Bachelor Degree with 70% and IELTS 6.5 Bands with 6.0 band in each module
                            </li>

                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div id="five" class="about-9-txt mb-40 pr-15 my-pt">

                        <!-- Title -->
                        <h3 class="h3-md mt-5">WORK RIGHTS
                        </h3>

                        <!-- Text -->
                        <p>
                            The Post-Graduation Work Permit Program allows students who have graduated from a participating Canadian post-secondary institution to gain valuable Canadian work experience.
                            <ul>
                                <li>Part time work right : Off campus 20 hours per week
                                </li>
                                <li>40 Hours per week during vacation. No limit for on campus work
                                </li>
                            </ul>

                            A work permit under the Post-Graduation Work Permit Program may be issued for the length of the study program, up to a maximum of three years.It cannot be valid for longer than the student’s study program, and the study program must be a minimum of eight months in length.
                        </p>


                    </div>
